                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>« <a href="/news-08-2018">August 2018</a> | <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="/news-09-2018">September 2018</a></span> | <a href="/news-10-2018">October 2018</a> »</strong></p>
</div>
<div style="border: 2px solid black; background-color: Moccasin;">
<p style="text-align: center;">The dynamic nature of this wiki means that linked pages might get moved, renamed, deleted, or replaced. Old news pages remain as time capsules and are not updated to account for these changes.</p>
</div>



<p><span style="font-size:75%;">This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</span></p>
<h4><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/halloween-contest-2018">Halloween Contest 2018</a> - The Bone Zone awakens! The 2018 Halloween contest kicks off October 5th, with 4 rules in place, all of them put in place for maximum spookiness. Readers beware, you're in for a scare.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Staff Promotions! This cycle, there were a total of 6 new Operational Staff and 3 new Moderators!
<ul>
<li>Junior Staff Promoted to Operational Staff: Captain Kirby, Fingo7, LadyKatie, Shaggydredlocks, taylor_itkin, and Varaxous!</li>
<li>Operational Staff promoted to Moderator: modern_erasmus, pxdnbluesoul, and MayD!</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>On October 20th at 1 PM, <a href="http://www.wasabicon.com/schedule/">Wasabicon</a> will be having an SCP panel! roget and procyonlotor are going to be there helping out with the panel, while several other SCPeople are planning to make an appearance (including djkaktus and doctor cimmerian). Hope we can see ya there!</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>The featured articles for this month were <a href="/scp-1387">SCP-1387</a> (&quot;Giant Seagull Airlines&quot;) by Waterfire, <a href="/in-the-clutches-of-life">In the Clutches of Life</a> by Captain Kirby, and <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/schulman-ny-programmable-mnestic-device-ac34d-nc77q-95dcs">'Schulman-NY Programmable Mnestic Device' (AC34D/NC77Q/95DCS)</a> by WrongJohnSilver and Cyantreuse.
<ul>
<li>In <a href="/scp-1387">SCP-1387</a>, a giant seagull decides to make its way into the airline industries.</li>
<li><a href="/in-the-clutches-of-life">In the Clutches of Life</a>. And with strange aeons even death may die.</li>
<li>In <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/schulman-ny-programmable-mnestic-device-ac34d-nc77q-95dcs">'Schulman-NY Programmable Mnestic Device' (AC34D/NC77Q/95DCS)</a>, we see just how much of your brain you really need to survive.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Event Featured Articles</span></h4>
<p>The theme for the month of September was <em>portal!</em></p>
<ul>
<li>In <a href="/scp-3941">SCP-3941</a> (&quot;The Major Occultation&quot;), by tufto, the Foundation engages in religous debate with the 12th Imam.</li>
<li>In <a href="/scp-1780">SCP-1780</a> (&quot;The Temporal Anomalies Department&quot;), by FortuneFavorsBold, a Foundation department is found, having been lost to all but time.</li>
<li>In <a href="/scp-1130">SCP-1130</a> (&quot;A Handy Shortcut&quot;), by Crayne, your destination is on your left, through the derelict entrance into an alternate reality.</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Editor's Choice</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4344">SCP-4344</a> (&quot;Kick Asteroid&quot;) by Weryllium</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p>A woefully underrated article. It's short, it's got dinosaurs, and they're <em>in space!</em> What more could you ask for?</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
