<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size:250%;"><strong>Fun contest facts!</strong></span></p>
<p><br />
This contest has brought out all sorts of characters from different walks of life, meaning that different Groups/Persons of Interest appearing was inevitable. Let's take a look at which G/PoI's came out to play!</p>
<ul>
<li>from <a href="/dado-hub">dado's fine laundry and tan</a> is dado himself yes</li>
<li>From <a href="/wilson-s-wildlife-solutions-hub">Wilson's Wildlife Solutions</a> hail <a href="/ringo">Ringo</a>, <a href="/critter-profile-wobbles">Wobbles</a>, and <a href="/critter-profile-maya">Maya</a>, some of the wildest contestants yet!</li>
<li><a href="/critter-profile-wobbles">Wobbles</a>, <a href="/ringo">Ringo</a>, and <a href="/maya-the-magnificent">Maya the Magnificent</a> have ties to other GoI; The Shark Punching Center , <a href="/chaos-insurgency-hub">The Chaos Insurgency</a> and <a href="/herman-fuller-hub">Herman Fuller's Circus of the Disquieting</a> respectively.</li>
<li><a href="/danger-in-the-manger">Heather Mason</a>, otherwise known as 'Ms. Mad About Video Games' is a <a href="/gamers-against-weed-hub">GAW</a> affiliated anomaly.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4799">Shock</a> has indirect ties to the <a href="/goc-hub-page">Global Occult Coalition.</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Since we're looking at the backgrounds of some characters, why not take a look and see what kind of article they came from as well?</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/the-summer-of-bad-memories">Ruslav Diaghilev</a>, <a href="/slice-of-life">Tyrone</a>, and <a href="/ethics">Agent Johnson</a> come from Tales.</li>
<li><a href="/ringo">Ringo</a>, <a href="/critter-profile-wobbles">Wobbles</a>, and <a href="/critter-profile-maya">Maya</a> all originated from GoI Format articles, with the lattermost even having a <a href="/maya-the-magnificent">double feature premiere!</a></li>
<li><a href="/scp-wow-j">Dr. Fynegan</a> is the only contestant originating from a Joke article.</li>
<li>All other contestants originated from a main-list SCP article.</li>
</ul>
<p>Assorted fun facts</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/a-romantic-comedy-starring-a-dead-mosquito-guest-starring-th">Let Her Heart DEET Once More</a> - by OthellotheCat was the first OCT entry posted in the contest.</li>
<li><a href="/the-antihero-by-dado">the antihero by dado</a> - by djkaktus was the last Round 1 OCT article posted.</li>
<li>Four entries used custom CSS themes, including <a href="/a-bearly-thought-out-plan">A Bear-ly Thought Out Plan</a> which uses the WWS Theme, <a href="/the-abyss-gazes-back">The Abyss Gazes Back (And It's ASCII On A CRT Screen)</a> uses the Pataphysics Theme, and <a href="/tyrone-joins-the-family">Tyrone Joins the Family</a> and <a href="/cater-duty">Cater Duty</a> both use the Spicy Crust Pizza theme.</li>
<li>Nine contestants (Maya, Gunhead Anomalocaris, Wobbles, Ringo, poky, Leslie, Tree Critter, Robber Ducks, Buddy, and Anoati) are non-humanoids.</li>
<li>Two entrants (Robber Ducks and poky) are more than one character, with poky bringing The Great Carnegias along for the ride, and Robber Ducks consisting of five separate entities.</li>
<li>The Plague Doctor is the oldest contestant in the OCT, with SCP-049 being posted on the 10th of December 2009.</li>
<li>In contrast; The Great Anoati is the youngest entrant, with SCP-3416 having been posted on the 24th of August 2018.</li>
<li>newyrose made custom Snapchat CSS for use in <a href="/grin-and-bear-it">Grin and Bear It</a> and <a href="/a-bearly-thought-out-plan">A Bear-ly Thought Out Plan.</a> She did an excellent job!</li>
<li><a href="/prehistoric-artillery-strike">Derailment By Prehistoric Artillery Strike</a> and <a class="newpage" href="/trilobastards">Trilobites: Many Reasons To Kill Them, and 0 Reasons Not To</a> are both tagged with 'interactive', meaning there's listpages magic afoot!</li>
<li><a href="/grin-and-bear-it">Grin and Bear It</a> and <a href="/a-bearly-thought-out-plan">A Bear-ly Thought Out Plan</a> tell a continuous story, and are the only Round 1 tales with a chronological order between contestants.</li>
<li>There were not one, but two ties in the contest, meaning there will be two three-way character meetings next round, not counting the Bonus Round contestants.</li>
<li>Nine Round 1 tale titles are puns. We'll let you figure out which ones they are.</li>
<li>Two Round 2 tales are song title references.</li>
<li>othellothecat was the first entrant to post their entry in Round 2. Fast fingers on this one!</li>
<li>othellothecat and gabriel jade tied again, this time the great hippo tied as well leading to the first three-way tie of the contest!</li>
<li><a href="/the-scent-of-a-toaster">The Scent of a Toaster</a> marks the start of the second season of <a href="/bird">Team Bird's</a> Doomcon canon!</li>
</ul>
